Cars45, an automotive trading platform has been recognized as a 2021 Automobile Leadership Excellence Prize winner. The award for its display of uncommon initiative and impressive developmental efforts in charging Africa’s economic aspirations through innovative and creative solutions. Cars45 was formally presented the prize at an awards ceremony in Lagos, which is in its fifth year organized by the African Institute for Leadership Excellence. Chief Executive Officer, Cars45, Soumobroto “Sunny” Ganguly, said the award marks a significant validation and ringing endorsement of their efforts at solving the challenges across the automotive value chain from new, to used, logistics, aftermarket and repair services and end-of-life vehicles.